In macroeconomics, '''SIMIC''' stands for '''Severely Indebted Middle Income Country'''. This was defined by the [[World Bank]] in 2004 as a country with an annual income of between $736 and $9,075 per capita, a debt/[[GNI]] ratio of at least 80%, and a debt/export ratio of at least 220%.<ref>http://www.palgrave.com/business/pilbeam_int/students/intros/15.htm</ref>

